    "Unlike Wadkin et al. (2023), we allow time-varying infestation rates β 1,t and β 2,t at each node, described by two independent Brownian motion processes, scaled by a common parameter σ β.",
    "The model takes the form of (25), with X t = (S 1,t, I 1,t, S 2,t, I 2,t, log β 1,t, log β 2,t) ′ and θ = (γ, α 1,2, α 2,1, σ β) ′.",
    "The drift and diffusion functions are given by",
    "The data (see Figure 5) consist of (noisy) observations of removal prevalence (R 1,t, R 2,t) ′, that is, the cumulative numbers of tree locations where nest removal has taken place, observed each year over the period 2013-2024.",
    "We assume a fixed number of tree locations (N j) at each node j so that S j,t + I j,t + R j,t = N j, j = 1, 2, and observation of removals is equivalent to observation of the sums S 1,t + I 1,t and S 2,t + I 2,t."
